The paper proposes a new complexity model for approximation algorithms and studies problems like Steiner Forest, Facility Location, k-Median, k-Center, and TSP in the case when the graph induces a doubling metric. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.CG (Computational Geometry), cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), cs.LG (Machine Learning), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). However, given the focus on data structures and algorithms, cs.DS is the most likely category, followed by cs.CG and cs.DM. The paper also discusses approximation guarantees, which could place it in cs.LG or cs.AI, but these categories are less likely given the emphasis on the complexity model and data structures.
